# Cadence retro (2026-05-27) — etude-8hq phase complete: roles, checklists, sidecar backfill

Cohort: etude-8hq.6 (reviewer roles/lenses), etude-8hq.7 (executable checklists),
etude-8hq.5 (backfill structured retro-meta sidecars + supersession-aware audit).
Beads 6-8 of phase etude-8hq — this CLOSES the phase (all 8 children + the epic shipped).

## Trigger
3-ticket cadence flagged by `dogfood-completeness-audit.sh` check (c). Carries a 7-key
sidecar (META=Y).

## What went well (preserve)
- **The phase landed its own thesis.** etude-8hq set out to move dogfood completeness
  "from memory into a mechanical close/push gate." It now is: close wrapper +
  `.beads/hooks/pre-push` hook + the full check suite (run/gate/pushed/cadence/
  cadence-sidecar/subject-consistency), and `make dogfood-audit` is fully clean.
- **The multi-seat gate kept catching real, escalating bugs to the very end.** 8hq.5's
  implement gate: codex found a Tier-1 MASKING hole (a post-cutoff cadence retro
  missing a sidecar could be hidden by superseding it with a non-validating ref) that
  gemini AND opus both GO'd. The not-a-vote-count rule (P3) made it decisive.
- **Faithful backfill, not fabrication.** The 10 cohort sidecars were extracted from
  each retro's body (empty arrays where the body had none).

## What went wrong / was caught late
- **cutoff × supersede interaction, twice.** 8hq.8 hit it first (superseding a
  pre-cutoff retro mints a post-cutoff ref that check (f) hard-gates) → pivoted to
  annotate. 8hq.5 hit the inverse (a skip applied BEFORE classification can mask a
  hard gap) → fixed by gating the check-(f) skip to pre-cutoff only. Root cause: a
  skip/exemption in a HARD gate must be applied AFTER the gate's own classification,
  never before — otherwise it bypasses the very check it sits in front of.
- **Epic-close needs allowlisting.** When the etude-8hq epic auto-closed, it entered
  the audit window as a runless closed bead → blocked the push until allowlisted
  (epics are rollups; children carry the runs). This recurs every phase.

## Durable changes landed
- 8hq.6: reviewer "lenses" (every seat applies all four); 8hq.7: compact
  `checklists.md` index; 8hq.5: supersession-aware audit + `f-mask-guard` regression
  test + the 17-retro sidecar/​re-tag backfill.
- This retro: the "skip/exemption AFTER classification in hard gates" lesson + the
  "allowlist the phase epic when it closes" note (ledger).

## Decision
informational — phase etude-8hq is complete; durable changes implemented.
